-- Edmund Kim Joins ONCAP, Robert Collins hired at GMP: Buzz
-- B y   K a t i a   D m i t r i e v a
-- 2013-05-17T18:39:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-17/edmund-kim-joins-oncap-robert-collins-hired-at-gmp-buzz.html
 Edmund Kim joined ONCAP Management
Partners in Toronto as a director from M/C Partners in  Boston 
where he was vice president, according to Vlaad and Co., a
Toronto-based financial services recruiting firm.  Other moves noted in “Bill’s Buzz”  newsletter  include:
*RBC Capital Markets chief institutional strategist Myles
Zyblock joined Dynamic Funds, a unit of Scotiabank, as chief
investment strategist.
*Ontario Teachers’ Pension Plan Board appointed Ron Mock as CEO,
replacing Jim Leech on Jan. 1, 2014.
*Robert Collins was hired as head of oil and gas corporate
finance at GMP Securities in the U.K. from Canaccord Genuity,
where he was natural resources head.
*Elizabeth Williamson was hired as corporate finance associate
in oil and gas group at GMP Securities in U.K. from Ophir
Energy.
*CIBC Global Asset Management appointed Suzann Pennington as
managing director and CIO.
*CIBC Global Asset Management appointed Marilyn Brophy as
managing director and head of equity research.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Katia Dmitrieva in Toronto at 
 edmitrieva1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
